WEBVTT

00:02.063 --> 00:04.050
Hello, my darlings!

00:04.156 --> 00:06.121
- How is everyone today?
- Hi.

00:06.233 --> 00:08.968
In good voice, I trust.

00:09.406 --> 00:11.037
Thank you.

00:11.071 --> 00:13.273
Bella, darling,
you know what I think we should do?

00:13.307 --> 00:15.975
I think we should simplify it.
Let the hosts come in, introduce me,

00:16.010 --> 00:17.583
we'll pitch the charity a little bit,

00:17.636 --> 00:20.880
Broadway hearts for hearts, and, um...

00:20.915 --> 00:22.982
And remember...
When she gets to the first

00:23.017 --> 00:25.318
"the things we do for love,"
stand by for snow drop.

00:25.352 --> 00:26.819
Shall we?

00:28.756 --> 00:31.558
This number has always
been one of my favorites...

00:32.317 --> 00:36.296
A classic love song from back in the day.

00:38.265 --> 00:39.785
Stand by for cue.

00:40.207 --> 00:44.404
Communication is the problem to the answer.

00:45.053 --> 00:48.866
You've got his number,
and your hand is on the phone.

00:49.261 --> 00:52.712
The weather's turned,
and all the lines are down.

00:52.746 --> 00:54.547
The things we do for love.

00:54.984 --> 00:57.250
- ♪ The things we do for love.
- Cue snow. Cue snow.

00:57.284 --> 00:59.919
♪ Like walking in the
rain and the snow ♪

00:59.954 --> 01:02.388
- ♪ And there's nowhere to go
- Get the snow going.

01:02.423 --> 01:06.726
♪ And you're feeling like
a part of you is dying ♪

01:06.760 --> 01:10.563
♪ And you're looking for
the answer in his eyes ♪

01:10.598 --> 01:11.431
Need more snow than that.

01:11.465 --> 01:13.499
♪ You think you're gonna break up ♪

01:13.534 --> 01:15.868
♪ Then he says he wants to make up ♪

01:18.572 --> 01:20.740
Oh, my God!

01:26.988 --> 01:30.550
So, captain Beckett,
have you successfully completed

01:30.584 --> 01:32.285
your agenda for your lunch meeting?

01:32.319 --> 01:33.920
Indeed I did... Three times.

01:33.954 --> 01:35.306
Three?

01:35.556 --> 01:36.623
Best meeting ever.

01:36.657 --> 01:38.191
Who would have thought

01:38.225 --> 01:39.859
that secret dating would be so productive?

01:39.893 --> 01:42.061
I know.
Our public fights have made

01:42.096 --> 01:44.731
- our private time so much more...
- Intense.

01:44.765 --> 01:46.366
- Right?
- Yes.

01:46.400 --> 01:48.768
I don't suppose the captain
has time for one more agenda?

01:48.802 --> 01:50.703
Oh, I'm sorry. I wish I could.

01:50.738 --> 01:53.573
But I have to make this meeting
with Captain Gates at 1PP.

01:53.607 --> 01:55.575
And is "Gates" code for "Vikram"

01:55.609 --> 01:58.511
and "1PP" your secret strip-club hideout?

01:58.814 --> 02:02.148
No. The meeting with Gates is very real.

02:02.182 --> 02:04.450
Look, Rick, I'm done playing lone wolf,

02:04.485 --> 02:07.120
and I promise you...
When the time is right,

02:07.154 --> 02:10.223
I will loop you in on everything Loksat.

02:12.693 --> 02:14.994
I-I mean,
I get that the whole thing is a covert op.

02:15.029 --> 02:17.764
I'm just saying...
I could be your secret weapon

02:17.798 --> 02:19.265
in taking Loksat down.

02:19.300 --> 02:22.001
Trust me, 007... When it's time,

02:22.036 --> 02:25.171
you and I will take down Loksat together.

02:25.205 --> 02:28.408
Meanwhile, I will be sneaking in and out

02:28.442 --> 02:31.077
of the building next door to get here.

02:31.111 --> 02:32.111
While I do what?

02:32.146 --> 02:34.013
Provide support and comfort.

02:34.048 --> 02:37.383
Lots and lots of comfort.

02:40.487 --> 02:41.454
Bye.

02:45.159 --> 02:46.693
Ah.

02:46.727 --> 02:47.694
Mother.

02:47.728 --> 02:49.095
How's your day going?

02:55.402 --> 02:56.536
Mother!

02:56.570 --> 02:58.638
Oh! Richard, darling.

02:58.672 --> 03:00.139
Thank God you're here.

03:00.174 --> 03:01.974
I came as soon as I could.

03:02.009 --> 03:04.143
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. Don't worry about me.

03:04.178 --> 03:06.846
It's poor, sweet Robyn that
we should be thinking about.

03:06.880 --> 03:08.681
- You knew her?
- I just met her yesterday.

03:08.716 --> 03:11.551
She... she sat through an entire rehearsal,

03:11.585 --> 03:12.852
and then she waited around

03:12.886 --> 03:14.687
so she could come up and thank me.

03:14.722 --> 03:17.690
She was just...

03:17.725 --> 03:18.891
She was lovely.

03:19.708 --> 03:20.860
Darling, I want you to promise me

03:20.894 --> 03:23.296
that you will handle this case personally

03:23.330 --> 03:25.038
and find out who did this.

03:25.766 --> 03:27.400
Yeah, of course. Of course.

03:27.434 --> 03:29.235
Gram, why don't I take you home?

03:29.269 --> 03:30.302
Okay.

03:30.355 --> 03:32.070
Perfect. Thank you. Okay.

03:32.956 --> 03:33.706
Hey.

03:33.741 --> 03:35.408
Hey. How's Martha?

03:35.442 --> 03:36.709
Uh, shaken up.

03:36.744 --> 03:38.154
What happened?

03:38.879 --> 03:41.514
Victim is Robyn King, 20 years old.

03:41.548 --> 03:43.549
Works as the theater's night janitor.

03:43.584 --> 03:46.552
Based on lividity and body temp,
I estimate the time of death

03:46.587 --> 03:49.155
is last night between 9:00 and 11:00.

03:49.189 --> 03:51.958
Cause of death... Blunt-force trauma.

03:53.193 --> 03:55.862
Killer hit Robyn in the head,
stuffed her in the snow box,

03:55.896 --> 03:57.330
and lifted her up to the rafter.

03:57.364 --> 03:58.531
Where she bled out.

03:58.565 --> 03:59.532
Yo.

03:59.566 --> 04:00.635
This is Chris Jackson.

04:00.754 --> 04:03.069
He's the theater's production manager.

04:03.103 --> 04:05.371
Richard Castle.
So, you're the one who hired Robyn?

04:05.406 --> 04:07.874
Yes. And I was a little nervous at first.

04:07.908 --> 04:09.776
Robyn was an ex-con,

04:09.810 --> 04:12.430
but her parole officer pressed
me to give her a job...

04:12.483 --> 04:14.714
Promised that she was
completely trustworthy.

04:14.748 --> 04:17.683
And until last night,
there hadn't been a single problem.

04:17.718 --> 04:19.285
What happened last night?

04:19.319 --> 04:21.921
A woman showed up looking for Robyn,

04:21.954 --> 04:23.473
and she was pissed.

04:23.539 --> 04:24.490
And Robyn knew her?

04:24.525 --> 04:26.350
Oh, yeah. She called her "mama."

04:26.455 --> 04:29.695
But they clearly weren't a happy family.

04:29.730 --> 04:32.198
As I was leaving,
I heard Robyn threaten to call the cops

04:32.232 --> 04:34.267
if her mom ever came near her again.

04:35.189 --> 04:37.128
I shouldn't have left them alone.

04:37.247 --> 04:41.641
Robyn might still be alive if I had just...
stayed behind.

04:42.524 --> 04:43.576
Hey.

04:43.610 --> 04:45.745
So, here's a surprise.

04:45.779 --> 04:49.148
Robyn's records show that her
mother died when she was 5.

04:49.183 --> 04:51.150
- Then who's "mama"?
- Exactly.

04:51.185 --> 04:53.286
And here's another mystery that I found...

04:53.320 --> 04:54.921
According to Robyn's metrocard,

04:54.955 --> 04:57.490
she's been taking subway
trips up to Spanish Harlem

04:57.524 --> 05:00.326
two nights a week ever since
she was released from prison.

05:00.360 --> 05:02.595
Each time, she leaves around 11:30 P.M.,

05:02.629 --> 05:05.231
stays for almost two
hours before going home.

05:05.265 --> 05:07.733
Any indication in her financials
what she's doing up there?

05:07.768 --> 05:08.734
No, nothing yet.

05:10.704 --> 05:12.104
- I got to take that.
- Okay.

05:12.139 --> 05:12.972
Hey!

05:13.006 --> 05:14.640
Hey. So, I heard about Martha.

05:14.675 --> 05:16.175
Why didn't you pull me out of the meeting?

05:16.210 --> 05:17.643
You know what? I thought about it.

05:17.678 --> 05:20.279
But this whole new...
secret relationship...

05:20.314 --> 05:21.647
I wasn't quite sure what the rules were.

05:21.682 --> 05:22.915
Well, I-is she okay?

05:22.950 --> 05:24.417
Physically, yes. She's fine.

05:24.451 --> 05:26.185
Emotionally, not so much.

05:26.220 --> 05:28.821
She made me promise to help
track down Robyn's killer.

05:28.856 --> 05:30.823
Of course, but you know that publicly,

05:30.858 --> 05:31.824
I can't agree to that.

05:31.859 --> 05:32.859
What do you mean?

05:32.893 --> 05:34.327
Well, it means that I love you,

05:34.361 --> 05:37.163
but right now,
I'm gonna have to yell at you.

05:39.466 --> 05:40.366
Castle!

05:40.400 --> 05:42.969
We talked about this! You can't be here!

05:43.003 --> 05:45.538
Well, excuse me for living,
but I've got a damn good reason.

05:45.572 --> 05:47.607
I don't care what your reason is.

05:47.641 --> 05:49.675
You can't just waltz in
and out of my precinct

05:49.710 --> 05:50.877
whenever you want.

05:50.911 --> 05:52.945
Uh, my mother was traumatized, Captain.

05:52.980 --> 05:54.947
I'm involved in this case,
whether you like it or not.

05:54.982 --> 05:57.683
Fine. But you're on a short leash.

05:57.718 --> 06:00.820
Oh, I'll decide how short my leash is.

06:01.755 --> 06:05.057
Yo. Just got off the phone
with Robyn's parole officer.

06:05.092 --> 06:06.826
Look who I found... Robyn's mama.

06:06.860 --> 06:08.794
Olivia "mama" Toussaint.

06:08.829 --> 06:11.364
She's a mid-level dealer who
sells party drugs to rich kids.

06:11.398 --> 06:13.799
Robyn was part of her crew two
years ago when she got busted.

06:13.834 --> 06:14.800
What was Robyn arrested for?

06:14.835 --> 06:17.470
Uh, grand theft auto,
reckless endangerment,

06:17.504 --> 06:18.704
destruction of private property.

06:18.739 --> 06:20.573
Robyn made a delivery to a country club

06:20.607 --> 06:22.508
on long island,
decided to stay for the party.

06:22.543 --> 06:24.544
She got wasted, stole a car,
drove into a house...

06:24.578 --> 06:26.145
Half a million dollars' worth of damage.

06:26.179 --> 06:28.214
Got her two years in albion correctional,
too.

06:28.248 --> 06:30.816
So, with Robyn out on parole,
mama must have gone

06:30.851 --> 06:32.685
to the theater to bring
her back into the fold.

06:32.719 --> 06:35.154
But Robyn refused and
threatened to rat mama out.

06:35.188 --> 06:37.356
So mama silenced Robyn for good.

06:37.391 --> 06:39.091
All right, boys, bring her in.

06:39.126 --> 06:40.826
All right.

06:42.596 --> 06:46.832
Tell me...
is the "mama" meant to be ironic?

06:46.867 --> 06:50.369
Not very motherly having
underage kids run drugs for you.

06:50.404 --> 06:52.204
I don't know what you're talking about.

06:52.239 --> 06:53.906
What about the name Robyn King?

06:53.941 --> 06:55.541
Does that ring a bell?

06:55.576 --> 06:57.043
Sure. What of it?

06:57.077 --> 06:58.744
She did two years in prison for you.

06:58.779 --> 07:01.514
You probably thought
the $40 a month you put

07:01.548 --> 07:03.950
in her prison commissary
account would keep her loyal.

07:03.984 --> 07:05.751
But I'm thinking it didn't.

07:05.786 --> 07:07.286
That's why you stopped by the theater

07:07.321 --> 07:09.388
to lay down a little
oldfashioned motherly guilt.

07:09.423 --> 07:12.458
Or was it to strong-arm
her back onto your crew?

07:12.492 --> 07:15.695
I went there to check on her,
make sure she was okay.

07:15.729 --> 07:17.930
We got a witness that says you
were angry when you showed up.

07:17.965 --> 07:20.299
What can I say? She hurt my feelings.

07:20.334 --> 07:21.801
Yeah. Kids.

07:21.835 --> 07:23.069
They don't call, they don't write.

07:23.103 --> 07:24.604
Tell me about it.

07:24.705 --> 07:26.205
You think they'd show a little gratitude

07:26.240 --> 07:28.351
instead of dumping you for a new family.

07:28.942 --> 07:30.676
Is that why you killed her?

07:30.711 --> 07:32.278
'Cause she started running
with that other crew?

07:32.312 --> 07:34.113
I didn't kill her, Detective.

07:34.148 --> 07:36.549
I went there, I said my piece, I left.

07:36.583 --> 07:37.717
And I can prove it.

07:37.751 --> 07:39.552
This new family...

07:39.586 --> 07:41.587
They wouldn't happen to live
in Spanish Harlem, would they?

07:41.622 --> 07:42.889
Hell if I know.

07:42.923 --> 07:45.191
Robyn said she hooked
up with them in prison

07:45.225 --> 07:47.393
and that they had a big thing coming up.

07:51.799 --> 07:53.800
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:53.834 --> 07:55.635
How'd it go with mama?

07:55.669 --> 07:58.304
Oh, her, uh, alibi checks out.

07:58.338 --> 08:00.106
She was in a cab by 8:15.

08:00.140 --> 08:04.777
And it looks as though Robyn
was working with a new crew.

08:04.812 --> 08:06.263
Uh...

08:06.847 --> 08:08.881
I had a really great time earlier.

08:08.916 --> 08:10.483
Me too.

08:10.517 --> 08:12.251
Is it wrong that I want
to kiss you right now?

08:12.286 --> 08:13.958
So wrong, it's right.

08:15.489 --> 08:17.657
- I'm sorry.
- For what?

08:17.691 --> 08:19.859
You're a jerk!

08:21.495 --> 08:23.229
Whoa.

08:23.263 --> 08:24.497
H-hey, bro, you okay?

08:24.531 --> 08:25.572
Yeah.

08:25.652 --> 08:27.900
No. Ow! Man, she hits hard.

08:27.935 --> 08:30.136
Look, Castle, I-it's clearly not okay,

08:30.170 --> 08:31.137
you being here.

08:31.171 --> 08:32.337
Yeah, you better go home.

08:32.371 --> 08:34.640
We'll call you if we find anything.

